   "body": "# Exam at a Glance\n\nEverything on this page comes from the **official CCAR-F Exam Guide v1.0**. Where a widely-circulated third-party claim disagrees with the guide, the guide wins and the third-party claim is flagged at the bottom.\n\n## The numbers\n\n| | |\n|---|---|\n| Exam code | **CCAR-F** |\n| Items | **60** |\n| Item format | **Multiple-choice *and* multiple-response.** Each item tells you how many options to select |\n| Structure | **4 scenarios, drawn at random from a bank of 6** |\n| Time | **120 minutes** |\n| Delivery | Proctored — online proctoring or a Pearson VUE test center |\n| Passing score | **720** on a scaled range of 100–1,000 |\n| Fee | **$125 USD** (partner-tier discounts apply at checkout) |\n| Validity | **12 months** from the award date |\n| Score report | Pass/fail + scaled score + **percent correct per domain** |\n\n## What it actually tests\n\nThe guide states the purpose plainly: it validates that you can make **informed decisions about tradeoffs** when building real solutions with Claude. It covers Claude Code, the Claude Agent SDK, the Claude API, and MCP.\n\nTwo consequences follow, and they shape how you should study:\n\n1. **Every item is scenario-based.** You are not asked to recall a flag; you are shown a production symptom and asked which change fixes it.\n2. **The right answer is the one that addresses the root cause, proportionately.** The sample questions in the guide are built around three recurring distractor types:\n   - **Valid but heavier than needed** — a real technique, applied where something cheaper would do (deploying a trained classifier when the prompt has never been given explicit criteria).\n   - **Fixes a different problem** — plausible, but aimed at a symptom that is not the one described (adding tool-*availability* routing when the failure is tool-*ordering*).\n   - **Does not exist** — an invented flag, env var, or config file.\n\n> When you narrow to two options, ask: *which one changes the thing the logs are actually blaming?* Then ask: *is there a lighter change that does the same job?*\n\n## Scoring\n\nThe exam is **criterion-referenced**: you are measured against a fixed standard, not against other candidates. The cut score of 720 was set through a formal standard-setting study of what a minimally-qualified candidate should achieve. Scaled scoring equates results across exam forms of slightly differing difficulty.\n\nThe per-domain percentages on your score report are **diagnostic only** — your pass/fail is determined by the total scaled score alone. A weak domain does not fail you by itself; it just tells you where you were weak.\n\n## Rules and logistics\n\n- **Closed book.** Your workspace must be clear of notes, books, phones, smart watches, headphones, and secondary monitors. You accept a non-disclosure agreement before the exam begins.\n- **Registration** runs through the Anthropic Partner Academy, with scheduling through Pearson VUE. You may cancel or reschedule up to 24 hours before; changes inside 24 hours forfeit the fee.\n- **Retakes** have escalating waiting periods: **14 days** after a first failure, **30 days** after a second, **90 days** after a third, with a maximum of **four attempts in a rolling 12-month period**. Each attempt costs the full fee.\n- **Renewal** before expiry is a **free, non-proctored assessment** on the Partner Academy. If the credential lapses, you retake the full exam at full price.\n\n## Where this comes from\n\n- **[The official CCAR-F Exam Guide (PDF)](https://everpath-course-content.s3-accelerate.amazonaws.com/instructor/6nizmqk8tpzpfjvt6qmmav7rh/public/1783542750/Claude+Certified+Architect+%E2%80%93+Foundations+Exam+Guide.pdf)** — v1.0, effective July 2026. Read it end to end; it is short, and it is the only document the exam is written against.\n- **[Anthropic Partner Academy](https://anthropic.skilljar.com)** — registration and the certification page.\n- **[docs.claude.com](https://docs.claude.com)** — for accuracy on anything the guide names but does not explain. When the docs seem to go further than the guide, the extra detail is out of scope.\n\n## Claims you may see elsewhere that the guide does not support\n\n| Claim in circulation | Status |\n|---|---|\n| \"The official learning path is 13 Academy courses\" | **Not in the guide.** The guide's preparation section (§7) prescribes *hands-on building*, not a course list. Courses may still help — but they are not the stated path |\n| \"The first 5,000 candidates test for free\" | Not in the guide. §11 says only that partner-tier discounts appear at checkout |\n| \"About 10 questions per scenario\" | Not stated. The guide gives 60 items and 4 scenarios; the rest is inference |",
   "ko": "**요지.** 60문항 · **multiple-choice + multiple-response 혼합**(각 문항이 몇 개 고르라고 명시) · 6개 시나리오 중 **4개 랜덤** · 120분 · **720/1000** · **$125** · 유효 **12개월** · closed-book.\n\n**판단 포인트 — 이 시험의 정체.** 가이드 §1이 못 박은 목적은 \"informed decisions about **tradeoffs**\". 즉 *암기가 아니라 제약 하의 판단*. 모든 문항이 프로덕션 증상을 주고 \"무엇을 바꿔야 하나\"를 묻는다.\n\n**오답 3유형** — 두 개로 좁혔을 때 이 렌즈로 가른다:\n1. **valid but heavier than needed** — 맞는 기법이지만 과설계 (프롬프트에 명시적 기준을 준 적도 없는데 분류기 모델부터 붙이기)\n2. **fixes a different problem** — 그럴듯하지만 로그가 지목한 원인이 아님 (문제는 도구 *순서*인데 도구 *가용성*을 손봄)\n3. **존재하지 않는 기능** — 없는 플래그·환경변수·설정파일\n\n> 두 선택지가 남으면: **\"로그가 실제로 탓하는 것을 바꾸는 쪽은 어느 것인가?\"** → 그다음 **\"같은 일을 더 가볍게 하는 방법이 있나?\"**\n\n**채점.** criterion-referenced(상대평가 아님). 도메인별 %는 **진단용이며 합격 판정에 안 쓰인다** — 총 scaled score만 본다.\n\n**행정.** Partner Academy 등록 → Pearson VUE 예약. 재응시 대기 **14 / 30 / 90일**, 롤링 12개월 내 **최대 4회**, 매회 정가. 만료 전 갱신은 **무료·비프록터** 평가, 만료 후엔 전체 재응시.\n\n**⚠️ 떠도는 오정보** — \"공식 학습경로 = 13개 Skilljar 코스\"·\"초기 5,000명 무료\"·\"시나리오당 10문항\"은 **모두 공식 가이드에 없다**. 가이드 §7의 준비 방법은 코스 목록이 아니라 **직접 만들어 보라**는 hands-on 7항목이다."
